  </style>

  <div class="container">
    <div style="background:rgba(196,149,106,0.1);border:1px solid rgba(196,149,106,0.25);border-radius:12px;padding:1rem 1.5rem;font-size:0.88rem;color:var(--text-secondary);line-height:1.6;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
      ✈️ <strong style="color:#C4956A;">Bangkok is 2026's most-visited city.</strong> With currency shifts making Southeast Asia even more affordable, flight planning matters more than ever. Check routes and jet lag below. <a href="https://gab.ae/news/currency-volatility-oil-crisis-travel-budgets-2026" style="color:#C4956A;">How currencies are shifting →</a>
    </div>
    <header>
      <h1>Flight Time Calculator</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Calculate <strong>estimated flight times</strong> between 50+ major airports worldwide. Get distances, time zone differences, and jet lag severity ratings instantly.</p>
    </header>

    <!-- Intro -->
    <section>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>Whether you're planning a long-haul trip or a quick regional hop, knowing the <strong>flight time</strong> between cities helps you plan layovers, manage jet lag, and set realistic arrival expectations. This calculator uses great circle distance and average cruising speeds to estimate your time in the air.</p>
        <p>Select your departure and arrival airports from over 50 major cities, and instantly see estimated flight duration, distance in both kilometers and miles, the time zone difference, and a jet lag severity rating. For routes without common direct flights, we show estimated connecting flight options through major hubs.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Calculator Config -->
    <section>
      <h2>Calculate Your Flight Time</h2>
      <div class="config-panel">
        <div class="config-grid">
