          <div class="total-label">Estimated Flight Time (non-stop)</div>
          <div class="route-label" id="route-label">—</div>
        </div>

        <div class="stats-grid" id="stats-grid">
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-label">Distance</div>
            <div class="stat-value" id="stat-km">0 km</div>
            <div class="stat-sub" id="stat-miles">0 miles</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-label">Time Zone Difference</div>
            <div class="stat-value" id="stat-tz">0 hours</div>
            <div class="stat-sub" id="stat-tz-detail">—</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-label">Jet Lag Severity</div>
            <div class="stat-value" id="stat-jetlag">None</div>
            <div class="stat-sub" id="stat-jetlag-detail">—</div>
            <div class="jetlag-meter"><div class="jetlag-fill" id="jetlag-fill"></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <div class="stat-label">Average Speed</div>
            <div class="stat-value">885 km/h</div>
            <div class="stat-sub">550 mph cruising speed</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="connecting-panel" id="connecting-panel" style="display:none">
          <h3>Connecting Flight Estimate</h3>
          <div class="stat-sub" style="margin-bottom:0.5rem" id="connecting-note">For routes without common direct service, here's an estimated connection:</div>
          <div class="connecting-route" id="connecting-route"></div>
          <div class="stat-sub" style="margin-top:0.75rem" id="connecting-total"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Busiest Routes Table -->
    <section>
      <h2>Top 25 Busiest Flight Routes</h2>
      <div class="table-container">
        <table id="routes-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th data-sort="rank"># <span class="sort-arrow"></span></th>
              <th data-sort="route">Route <span class="sort-arrow"></span></th>
              <th data-sort="distance">Distance <span class="sort-arrow"></span></th>
              <th data-sort="time">Avg. Flight Time <span class="sort-arrow"></span></th>
              <th data-sort="freq">Daily Flights <span class="sort-arrow"></span></th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody id="routes-body"></tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Longest Flights -->
    <section>
      <h2>Longest Non-Stop Flights in the World</h2>
      <div class="table-container">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>#</th>
              <th>Route</th>
              <th>Airline</th>
              <th>Distance</th>
              <th>Flight Time</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody id="longest-body"></tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section>
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How is flight time calculated?</h3>
        <p>Flight time is estimated using the great circle distance between two airports divided by an average cruising speed of 885 km/h (550 mph). The great circle distance is the shortest path between two points on a sphere, calculated using the Haversine formula with each airport's latitude and longitude coordinates. Actual flight times may vary due to wind, routing, and air traffic.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Why are actual flight times different from estimates?</h3>
        <p>Estimated flight times can differ from actual times by 30-60 minutes due to several factors: jet stream winds (headwinds add time, tailwinds reduce it), air traffic control routing that may not follow the shortest path, time spent taxiing on the ground, takeoff and landing procedures, and detours around restricted airspace or weather systems.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What is jet lag and how long does it last?</h3>
        <p>Jet lag is a temporary sleep disorder caused by crossing multiple time zones. Symptoms include fatigue, insomnia, difficulty concentrating, and digestive issues. As a rule of thumb, it takes about one day per time zone crossed to fully adjust. Traveling eastward is generally harder to recover from than traveling westward because it's easier to extend your day than shorten it.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What is the longest non-stop flight in the world?</h3>
        <p>The longest non-stop commercial flight is Singapore Airlines' route from Singapore to New York (SIN-JFK), covering approximately 15,349 km (9,537 miles) in about 18 hours and 40 minutes. Other ultra-long routes include Auckland to Doha (14,526 km), Perth to London (14,498 km), and Singapore to Los Angeles (14,114 km).</p>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How do connecting flights affect total travel time?</h3>
        <p>Connecting flights typically add 3-6 hours to your total travel time compared to direct flights. This includes the layover time (usually 1.5-3 hours for domestic connections and 2-4 hours for international), plus the additional flight segments which may not follow the most direct route. Some routes have no direct flights, making connections unavoidable.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Related pages -->
    <section>
      <h2>Related Pages</h2>
      <div class="related-grid">
        <a href="/travel-budget-calculator" class="related-card">
          <h3>Travel Budget Calculator</h3>
          <p>Plan your trip budget by destination &rarr;</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/packing-list-generator" class="related-card">
          <h3>Packing List Generator</h3>
          <p>Build a custom packing checklist for any trip &rarr;</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/digital-nomad-visa-guide" class="related-card">
          <h3>Digital Nomad Visa Guide</h3>
          <p>Compare remote work visas across 32 countries &rarr;</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

